text: My @KinoLorber order is now here in Nashville, but it's not scheduled to be delivered for another week. What will @FedEx do next?
@TheIndieHandbk Hi, this is Giovanni. I would be happy to check on your shipment. Please DM your full name ,address, tracking, email address, and phone number. Thank you. https://t.co/7vnSkvqx3r

@FedExHelp It's ok. I'm sure it will arrive on time. I'm just wondering if it will arrive early. Once, the post office sent my package to Puerto Rico because it got to town a week ahead of time, just so I wouldn't get it early.
@TheIndieHandbk I understand. Please Monitor https://t.co/86Ngq6W0fh for any updated scans that show the package on a vehicle for delivery. Thank you. -Giovanni

I live in the Nashville suburbs. This morning, my @KinoLorber package arrived in Nashville. Tonight, it was sent to Mississippi. Why? I think it's because @FedEx can't bear to deliver it early. That, or @FedEx is run by idiots. Maybe both. https://t.co/Zy0oLIcqVq
